# Dev Debug AI Environment

-------------The below is the link to view the agent flow --------------------------------------------

https://RAJTZCODE-dev-debug-env.hf.space/docs

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

## 🚀 Overview

This project simulates a real-world software development workflow where an AI agent learns how to debug code, manage features, and optimize code quality under time constraints.

Unlike simple environments, this system models realistic developer behavior such as reading logs before fixing bugs and balancing feature development with code quality.

---
## 🧠 Environment Design

### State (Observation)

* `bugs`: Number of bugs in the system
* `code_quality`: Code quality score
* `features`: Number of completed features
* `deadline`: Remaining time steps
* `logs`: List of system error logs

---
### Actions

* `read_logs` → Understand issues before fixing
* `fix_bug` → Reduce bugs (better after reading logs)
* `write_feature` → Add features but may introduce bugs
* `refactor_code` → Improve code quality
* `do_nothing` → Penalized

---
## 🎯 Tasks

### Easy

Fix all bugs.

### Medium

Build at least 2 features with minimal bugs.

### Hard

Optimize:

* Features
* Bugs
* Code quality
* Deadline

---
## 🏆 Reward Design

* Positive reward for meaningful actions
* Higher reward for fixing bugs after reading logs
* Penalty for inefficient or wasteful actions
* Encourages strategic decision-making

---
## 🤖 Inference

Run:

uvicorn main:app --reload
python inference.py

---
## 📦 Deployment

This project is containerized using Docker and deployable on Hugging Face Spaces.

---
## 💡 Why This Matters

This environment models real developer workflows and can be used to train AI agents for debugging and decision-making in software engineering tasks.
